from the Temple of Victory and red-figure craters being the principle pieces) and a numismatic gallery then follow before the main room which contains Hellenistic and Roman material from Termini Imerese itself. Small finds, sculpture and inscriptions predominate. The museum collection continues upstairs with non-archaeological material (and a single inscription). The courtyard of the building holds a large collection of architectural pieces and inscriptions",{"settlement":91,"region":129,"country":130,"address":131,"geo":132},"Palermo","Italy","Via Marco Tullio Cicerone, 90018 - Termini Imerese (PA)",{"lat":133,"lon":134},37.98655109,13.69587845,{"_":136,"type":137},"91","inventory",{"_":139,"mainLang":140,"languages":141},"Latin","la",[139],{"type":143,"bibl":144},"edition",[145,153,163,174,184,200,211],{"author":146,"date":102,"citedRange":147,"ptr":148,"ref":149,"inscriptionDate":102,"title":150,"citation":151,"uri":152,"year":102},"Gualtherus","93",{"target":149},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GIN6NANU","Siciliae obiacentium insular et Bruttiorum antiquae tabulae cum animadversionibus Georgii Gualtheri","\u003Cspan>G. Gualtherus, \u003Ci>Siciliae obiacentium insular et Bruttiorum antiquae tabulae cum animadversionibus Georgii Gualtheri\u003C/i> (Panormi, 1624)\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/GIN6NANU",{"author":146,"date":154,"citedRange":155,"ptr":156,"ref":158,"inscriptionDate":154,"title":160,"citation":161,"uri":162,"year":102},"1624 [1625]","256",{"target":157},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/ZP8DE8KS",{"_":159,"target":159},"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001931","Siciliæ obiacentium insular. et Bruttiorum antiquæ tabulæ, cum animadversionib","\u003Cspan>G. Gualtherus, \u003Ci>Siciliæ obiacentium insular. et Bruttiorum antiquæ tabulæ, cum animadversionib\u003C/i> (Messanae: apvd Petrvs Bream, 1624), \u003Ca href=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/Gualtieri1624\">http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/G